        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>updateGeometry</name>
        <qualifiedname>Quick3DTerrainGeometry::updateGeometry</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Regenerates the terrain mesh geometry from current height data.</para>
<para>This method constructs a triangulated grid by generating vertex positions, per-vertex normals, and UV texture coordinates. The mesh is built using a resolution×resolution grid where each quad is split into two triangles. Vertex normals are calculated using the cross product of adjacent edges for proper lighting. The geometry buffers are uploaded to the GPU through Qt Quick 3D&apos;s geometry API. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
